            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2022-05-30 16:20:08" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(derivative of {L:χαρίζομαι&lt;SDBG:χαρίζομαι:000000&gt;}[a] ‘to give graciously and generously,’ {D:57.102}) that which is given freely and generously</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>gift</Gloss>
                <Gloss>gracious gift</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>χάρις[b] may also occur in contexts in which the meaning of ‘generous gift’ may imply the purpose of gaining some favor or benefit. In {S:04402402700024} (θέλων τε χάριτα καταθέσθαι τοῖς Ἰουδαίοις ὁ Φῆλιξ ‘Felix wanted to be offered a generous gift by the Jews’) the implication is that of ‘a bribe,’ but probably spoken of euphemistically here as ‘a gift.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
